sp.p:
Yes if I lik'd that other better than him; but e're I forſook
him I'de be ſure of one, That ſhou'd ſupply his plaec when he were gone;
and one who'd inſtantly marry me:

                     Why, and I did the like by this Letter here.
which I receiv'd and read on Curioſity, mere Curioſity;
with intent to laugh afterwards, and make me ſport at all he writes.

Thou mak'ſt me happy; for by this time,
ſhe loves me then, and can no longer doubt of my affection;
for my Father—

Well, perchance he may have told you true; but he is not often
guilty of that fault; wherefore knowing him as you do, precipitate nothing;
let me adviſe you.
